body.p:
Statistics show better than any discourse the extent of the Jewish invasion into Hungarian
				life. If we limit our analysis to Budapest, which sums up
				the general situation, we will find the following percentages in 1935: bankers 80%; transport 70%;
				stockbrokers 76%; 
 jewellers 74%; typographers 73%; owners of public establishments 57%;
					lawyers 52%; doctors 40%; journalists 35%.
